new cat hiding in basement we have a year old male tabby cat elmo who was an only pet and then we added a pit bull now month old stella a month and a half ago this guy died and his year old domestic shorthair cat skippy was in the house with him for a while and then was rescued the rescuer couldn't keep him so for lack of another home we took him in elmo and stella have a weird friendship stella is eager to play and elmo misses being the only pet so he swats at the puppy and bites her but the puppy just loves him chases after him and likes to play when i brought skippy in elmo decided to befriend stella unite against the intruder skippy took to the basement and will not come up he hates elmos and stella hisses has hit them pretty hard with his paws i'm wondering if skippy will ever blend in and if not how can i help him be happy give them all a little time the new cat has a lot to adjust to it will just take some patience on your part let skippy hide in the basement for a while until he feels less stressed just make sure to go down and give him some affection every day and make sure he keeps eating and drinking they may never be the best of friends but they will adjust to each other Cat St. Elmo's Fire (film) Dog Sin City Avenue Q Calvin and Hobbes 2000 Australian Grand Prix Elmo One Piece minor characters RuneScape quests W.I.T.C.H. Fancy rat Garfield Maine Coon Kim Possible Skinny Puppy Shaggy dog story Pitaten Azumanga Daioh Dead Like Me Dean Koontz Turkish Van Ron and Fez Blood on the Tracks The Legend of Zelda series enemies The Ashlee Simpson Show Pet skunk Housebreaking Nine Inch Nails Flamingo Road One Tree Hill (TV series) Hey Arnold! Minor characters in Sonic the Hedgehog Negima The League of Gentlemen (comedy) Sesame Street Lorraine Baines McFly Bengal cat The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy AFI 100 Years series Les contes d'Hoffmann Eek! The Cat I Want to Hold Your Hand Characters in the Smurfs The Smoking Room Sesame Street, Season 35 Winx Club El Go